\subsection{The Meta-Analytical Function ($\Gamma$)}
The $\Gamma$ function consists of two critical, interacting methods.

\subsubsection{Component $\Gamma_1$: Self-Awareness}
Method \texttt{\_check\_system\_paradox()} scans for \textit{Systemic Self-Contradiction (Pattern SC)} \cite{xenopoulou2024xdpas}.

\textbf{Source Reference:} \url{https://github.com/kxenopoulou/xenopoulos_dialectical-paradoxes-XEPTQLRI/blob/main/src/self_correction.py#L101-L135}

\subsubsection{Component $\Gamma_2$: Auto-Correction}
Method \texttt{\_generate\_fixed\_recommendations()} synthesizes new rules upon paradox diagnosis \cite{xenopoulou2024xdpas}. Key rule: \texttt{if attention\_level == "ΚΡΙΣΙΜΟ": add\_immediate\_action()}.

\textbf{Source Reference:} \url{https://github.com/kxenopoulou/xenopoulos_dialectical-paradoxes-XEPTQLRI/blob/main/src/self_correction.py#L67-L99}

\subsubsection{The Complete $\Gamma$ Loop}
The main report generation method integrates $\Phi$ and $\Gamma$, closing the loop \cite{xenopoulou2024xdpas}.

